  "prompt": "How do I recover my Gmail password with a recovery mobile number and a Gmail address?",
  "response": "If you need to recover your Gmail password using a recovery mobile number and your Gmail address, follow these steps:\n\n1. **Go to the Google Account Recovery Page**:\n   - Open a web browser and go to the [Google Account Recovery page](https://accounts.google.com/signin/recovery).\n\n2. **Enter Your Email Address**:\n   - Type in the Gmail address for which you want to recover the password and click on \"Next\".\n\n3. **Select 'Forgot Password?'**: \n   - When prompted to enter your password and you can't remember it, click on the \"Forgot password?\" link.\n\n4. **Verification Options**:\n   - You will be prompted with several recovery options. Since you have a recovery mobile number set up, choose the option to receive a verification code to that mobile number. \n\n5. **Receive and Enter the Verification Code**:\n   - Google will send a verification code to your recovery mobile number. Check your phone for a text message with the code.\n   - Enter the code into the provided field and click \"Next\".\n\n6. **Set a New Password**:\n   - Once your identity is verified, you will be prompted to create a new password. Choose a strong password that you haven\u2019t used before. \n   - Confirm the new password by entering it again.\n\n7. **Complete the Recovery**:\n   - After entering your new password, click \"Next\" or \"Save\" to finalize the process. You should now be able to log in with your new password.\n\n8. **Review Account Recovery Options**:\n   - Once you regain access to your Gmail account, it\u2019s a good idea to review your security settings. Make sure your recovery options (email addresses and phone numbers) are up-to-date in case you need to recover your account again in the future.\n\nIf you do not have access to your recovery mobile number, follow the prompts for the alternate recovery methods offered by Google, such as answering security questions or using a backup email address if one is associated with your account.",
